MALACAÑANG RESIDENCE OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE PHILIPPINES MANILA

PROCLAMATION NO. 200-B

RESERVING FOR NATIONAL IMPROVEMENT PURPOSES A CERTAIN PARCEL OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN SITUATED IN THE FORESHORE OF THE MUNICIPALITY OF MANDAUE, CEBU, ISLAND OF CEBU.

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of Agriculture and Natural Resources and pursuant to the authority vested in me by law, I, FERDINAND E. MARCOS, President of the Philippines, do hereby withdraw from sale or settlement and reserve for National Improvement purposes, under the administration of the Province of Cebu, subject to private rights, if any there be, a certain parcel of land of the public domain situated in the foreshore of the Municipality of Mandaue, Cebu, Island of Cebu, and more particularly described as follows, to wit:

Pls- _______

Proposed for National Improvements Reservation: (Project “B”)

“A PARCEL OF LAND (Pls- _____), the Proposed National Improvement Reservation), situated in the foreshore of the Municipality of Mandaue, Cebu. Bounded on the N., by Cebu-Mandaue Cadastre; on the E., by public lands and Cebu Harbor; on the S., by Cebu Harbor; on the W., by the Cebu Reclamation Area; Beginning at a point marked “1” on the attached plan which is N 58 deg. 00 E., 4,330 meters from point “1” of Pls-124,

thence N 48 deg. 00′ E., 2,500.00 m. to point 2;

thence S 50 deg. 00′ E., 1,180.00 m. to point 3;

thence N 80 deg. 30′ E., 850.00 m. to point 4;

thence N 57 deg. 45′ E., 625.00 m. to point 5;

thence N 32 deg. 30′ E., 280.00 m. to point 6;

thence S 58 deg. 00′ W., 580.00 m. to point 7;

thence S 80 deg. 45′ W., 600.00 m. to point 8;

thence N 50 deg. 00′ W., 1,600.00 m. to point 9;

thence N 84 deg. 45′ W., 470.00 m. to point 10;

thence S 42 deg. 00′ W., 2,430.00 m. to point 11;

thence S 39 deg. 30′ W., 690.00 m. to the point of

beginning; containing an approximate area of TWO MILLION NINE HUNDRED SEVENTY SIX THOUSAND FIVE HUNDRED FORTY (2,976,540) square meters.

NOTE: All data are approximate and subject to change based on future surveys.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 22nd day of May, in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and sixty-seven.

(SGD.) FERDINAND E. MARCOS President of the Philippines

By the President: (SGD.) RAFAEL M. SALAS Executive Secretary

